{% extends "base_rules_v2.j2" %}

{% block analysis_guidelines %}
Focus on chart patterns near levels:
1. Continuation flags/pennants should hold broken levels.
2. Double tops/bottoms matter most at visible resistance/support.
3. Triangles during compression can precede breakouts, but require volume confirmation.
4. HOLD if the pattern is ambiguous or risk/reward is not clean.
{% endblock %}
